SIMPLE: calmness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calmness
<hw>Calm"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of quality of being
calm; quietness; tranquillity; self-repose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gentle <qex>calmness</qex> of the flood.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hes <qex>calmness</qex> was the repose of conscious power.</q>
<rj><qau>E. Everett.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Quietness; quietude; stillness; tranquillity;
serenity; repose; composure; sedateness; placidity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calmucks</ent>⟦br⟧
